Governor Seyi Makinde of Oyo State has Monday, inaugurated sixty-eight caretaker committee chairpersons in all the thirty three Local Government Areas (LGAs) and thirty five Local Council Development Areas (LCDAs) in the state. The inauguration took place at the Agodi Government Secretariat in Ibadan, the state capital amids funfare. The Governor while speaking said that the caretakers would be the link between the state government and the people at the grassroots. “We inaugurated the Local Government and Local Community Development Areas Caretaker Chairpersons, this morning. “They will be the link between the State Government and the people. “We know that the closer government is to the people, the more impactful and meaningful its activities will be to them.” Makinde also enjoyed them to contribute their meaningful quota to the development of the state. He said “I enjoined all sixty-eight Caretaker Chairpersons to contribute their meaningful quota to ensure that we move Oyo State forwards, as they play their role along with the State Government to implement our Roadmap to Accelerated Development of Oyo State 2019-2023.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.